Template design pattern is a behavioural design pattern defines the basic structure of an algorithm
in superclass and allowing subclasses to provide specific implementations of certain steps of the
algorithm without modifying its overall structure. It promotes code reuse and enforces a common
algorithm structure across multiple subclasses.


1. Sending notification either through email or through SMS involves preparation of notification ,
creation of message and sending of message as basic steps , so here we can define a common template
that contains all the basic steps of sending notification and this template is implemented by email and SMS class